title: NO2 concentration (ppb) by U.S. Census Block Group - Minneapolis/St Paul
name: NO2 concentration (ppb) by U.S. Census Block Group - Minneapolis/St Paul
description:
Year-2006 annual average ground-level nitrogen dioxide (NO2) concentration estimates at the U.S. Census Block Group level. Based on U.S. Census Block level estimates from a land use regression model for the contiguous United States.

Details about the data set are published here:
EV Novotny, MJ Bechle, DB Millet, JD Marshall, "National satellite-based land-use regression: NO2 in the United States," Environmental Science & Technology, 45(10), 4407â€“4414, (2011).
